('14ae7c5a28bcb4', 'FMledgerselect', 'Ledger', NULL, '', '', '1', NULL, 'SELECT * FROM ledger', 'ledger', 'ledger_id', '1', '1', '1', '1', '', NULL, '', '', '', '', '', NULL, '', 'SELECT ''#led_built_in#'' != ''1'' ', '', 'SELECT ''#led_built_in#'' != ''1'' ', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '0', '', '', '<h3> Ledger Codes </h3>\r\nWhen ledger accounts are created they are given an autogenerated code that is defined from it''s parent ledger and follows a few select rules\r\n</br></br>\r\nThere are 8 different areas of accounting, each starts with it''s own special number (1-8). For each area a built in master ledger account exists. These are given codes of the form 1-0000, 2-0000 etc. For example Assets is given the code 1-0000.\r\n</br></br>\r\nBuilt in accounts cannot be deleted or modified in anyway. Subsequently any account that is currently in use, has been used in the past or is considered a parent of another account is protected and cannot be deleted or modified.\r\n</br></br>\r\nWhen a new account is added and considers a master account as it''s parent (eg X-0000) then it has a list of free codes autogenerated in the form X-YY00 where YY is a free number from 1 - 99. So for example if the account 2-0000 is chosen as the parent account and all accounts from 2-0100 to 2-1500 have all ready been allocated then the codes 2-1600 to 2-9900 will be selectable from the list.\r\n</br></br>\r\nWhen a new account is added and considers it''s parent is in the 2nd level of accounts (eg of the form X-XX00) then it has a list of free codes autogenerated in the form X-XXY0 where Y is the next free number from 1 - 9. So for example if account 2-1600 is chosen as the parent account and all accounts from 2-1610 to 2-1650 have all ready been allocated then the codes 2-1660 to 2-1690 will be selectable.\r\n</br></br>\r\nWhen a new account is added and considers it''s parent is in the 3rd level of accounts (eg of the form X-XXX0) then it has a list of free codes autogenerated in the form X-XXXY where Y is the next free number from 1 - 9. So for example if account 2-1660 is chosen as the parent account and all accounts from 2-1661 to 2-1665 have all ready been allocated then the codes 2-1666 to 2-1669 will be selectable.\r\n</br></br>\r\n<h3> Warnings </h3>\r\nThere are only 4 levels of accounts possible in the financial module. Therefore if you choose an account of the from X-XXXX you will be given a warning message that this account is not able to be used as a parent.\r\n</br></br>\r\nIf an account level has all slots for children occupied then a warning message will be outputted warning the user to choose another parent ledger. For example if you select 2-1600 as the parent ledger and all codes from 2-1610 to 2-1690 have been allocated the warning will be given.\r\n', '0', '2009-10-28 14:46:34', '2009-11-11 16:10:00', 'globeadmin', '', NULL, 0, 0, 0, ''),
